Review: login lockout and countdown
Commit scope:
- src/main/java/com/inote/controller/AuthController.java
- src/main/java/com/inote/config/GlobalExceptionHandler.java
- src/main/java/com/inote/service/AuthService.java
- src/main/java/com/inote/service/LoginLockService.java
- src/main/java/com/inote/service/LoginLockException.java
- web/src/App.tsx
- web/src/api.ts
- web/src/components/AuthView.tsx

Findings:
- [suggestion] The lock state is stored only in-process in `LoginLockService`, so it will not be shared across multiple app instances or survive restarts. If this project is ever deployed behind a load balancer, the 60-second lock can be bypassed by hitting a different node.

Summary:
- The 5-failure lockout, server-side 60-second rejection, and frontend countdown are implemented coherently.
- No blocking defect was found in the single-instance path.
